Reasoning: The paper proposes a new model of rarity and randomness assessment that is designed to be cognitively plausible, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model is also tested on Lottery sequences, which could fall under computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the pervasiveness of rarity assessment in spontaneous narrative behavior, which could relate to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
